The '''National Union for the Liberation of Cabinda''' ({{lang-pt|'''União Nacional de Libertação de Cabinda'''}}; '''UNLC''') is a militant separatist group fighting for the independence of [[Cabinda (province)|Cabinda]] from [[Angola]]. The UNLC emerged in the 1990s under the leadership of Lumingu Luis Gimby during the [[Angolan Civil War]].<ref name="groups">[http://www.globalsecurity.org/military/world/para/flec.htm Front for the Liberation of the Enclave of Cabinda (Frente para a Libertação do Enclave de Cabinda—FLEC)] Global Security</ref>

