== Media == Devore has been an educator and media spokesperson on intersex issues since 1984 when he appeared on ''Oprah''.<ref name="sf-gate" /> He has appeared in documentaries for [[Discovery Channel]] (2000),<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.tigerdevorephd.com/2000/12/31/is-it-a-boy-or-a-girl/ | title = “Is It a Boy or a Girl?” | work = [[Discovery Channel]] | date = 2000}}</ref> [[PBS]], [[National Geographic Channel]] television, the [[British Broadcasting Corporation]], and the award-winning short movie ''[[XXXY (film)|XXXY]]'' by [[Stanford University]].<ref>{{cite web | url = http://vimeo.com/66443054 | title = XXXY | work = [[XXXY (film)]] via [[Advocates for Informed Choice#The Interface Project|The Interface Project]] on [[Vimeo]] | date = 2000}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news| last = Greenhouse| first = Emily| title = A new era for intersex rights| work = The New Yorker| date = December 30, 2015| url = http://www.newyorker.com/news/news-desk/a-new-era-for-intersex-rights | accessdate = 2018-11-30}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book| isbn = 978-1-62313-502-7| last = Human Rights Watch| title = “I Want to Be Like Nature Made Me”| accessdate = 2018-11-30| date = July 2017| url = https://www.hrw.org/report/2017/07/25/i-want-be-nature-made-me/medically-unnecessary-surgeries-intersex-children-us | work = [[Human Rights Watch]]}}</ref> Devore is also interviewed in the 2012 documentary ''[[Intersexion]]''. In 2013, he was interviewed by ''[[Time Magazine]]'' on the then-new German birth certificate laws, and called for a global ban on "normalizing surgeries."<ref>{{cite web | url = http://world.time.com/2013/11/12/boy-girl-or-intersex/ | title = Boy, Girl or Intersex? Germany adjusts to a third option at birth | work = [[Time Magazine]] | date = November 12, 2013}}</ref>
